getCurrentCycle().details: Cycle counting begins at 1, not 0. Cycle 0 is a special case that only occurs when interacting directly with the contract while the pool is not live. This special case is handled by returning 0 when the pool is not in the Live state. Within the contract's logic, all meaningful operations are performed using cycles > 0

returns.currentCycle: The current cycle number, or 0 if the pool is not live
